'''英钱'''（{{lang-en|pennyweight}}，缩写：'''dwt'''），或译为'''本尼威特'''、'''便士重'''，英美重量单位，等于24[[格令|格令]]、'''{{frac|20}}'''[[金衡盎司|金衡盎司]]或'''{{frac|240}}'''[[金衡|金衡]]磅，约等于0.054857[[盎司|常衡盎司]]<ref>换算关系：<br/>
:1 常衡盎司 = 437.5 格令<br/>
:1 金衡盎司 = 480 格令</ref>或1.55517384 [[克|克]]。<ref>换算关系：<br/>
:1 金衡格令 = 0.06479891 克 （精确定义）</ref>

== 历史 ==
在中世纪，一个{{le|古便士|Penny (British pre-decimal coin)|英国便士}}的重量是相差无几的，在货币方面，1便士等于'''{{frac|20}}'''盎司或'''{{frac|240}}'''{{le|标准纯银|sterling silver}}磅。当时所用的磅是[[塔磅|塔磅]]。中世纪的英国便士等于32塔衡格令（也称麦格令）。1527年，金衡制代替塔衡制，在金衡制中，旧的塔衡磅等于5400金衡格令（也称巴利肯/大麦粒），塔衡英钱为22'''{{frac|2}}'''金衡格令，约等于1.46克。1527年后，英钱改用金衡制英钱。<ref>{{cite book| last = Zupko| first = Ronald Edward| authorlink = Ronald Edward Zupko| title = A dictionary of weights and measures for the British Isles| publisher = American Philosophical Society| year = 1985| pages = 280–84| url = http://books.google.com/books?id=0l_k-XMIiQIC&pg=PA283&dq=pennyweight&hl=en&ei=en_ATrmDKNDciQLr7dHAAw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CEIQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=pennyweight&f=false| isbn = 978-0-87169-168-2| access-date = 2014-12-20| archive-date = 2017-06-24| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170624082952/https://books.google.com/books?id=0l_k-XMIiQIC&pg=PA283&dq=pennyweight&hl=en&ei=en_ATrmDKNDciQLr7dHAAw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CEIQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=pennyweight&f=false| dead-url = no}}</ref>

== 应用 ==
在1878年的《{{le|重量及计量条例|Weights and Measures Act}}》中，金衡磅和英钱已失去了在英国的法定单位地位；仅金衡盎司及其十进制辅助单位仍具法定地位。金衡盎司在英国享有特殊的免除{{le|米制化|Metrication}}的法律地位。<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/1985/72 |title= Weights and Measures Act 1985 |date= 2011-08-30 |accessdate= 2011-09-22 |quote= Part II Weighing and Measuring for Trade ... 8 Units of measurement, weights and measures lawful for use for trade ... (2) No person shall use for trade—(a) the ounce troy, except for the purposes of transactions in, or in articles made from, gold, silver or other precious metals, including transactions in gold or silver thread, lace or fringe... |archive-date= 2022-01-02 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20220102140420/https://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/1985/72 |dead-url= no }}</ref>

英钱是贵金属估值和测量时的常见单位。珠宝商利用英钱来计算在制作珠宝时贵金属的使用量和成本。同时，牙医和牙科实验室也仍使用英钱来计量牙套和牙齿镶补所用的贵金属。<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.maguireref.com/index.cfm?Page=Calculator |title= Precious Metal Buyers, Gold Refiners, Gold Assayers, Waste Management |accessdate= 2011-09-22 |date= 2011-09-22 |format=  |work= Precious metals calculator |publisher= Maguire & Strickland Refining |quote= This section is for those in the trade. Those in the trade include jewelers, dentists and dental laboratories who have a store front, State ID numbers and Federal ID numbers ... We do not list a dental estimating factor as there is no standard gold percentage for dental solids |archive-date= 2012-04-02 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20120402183707/http://www.maguireref.com/index.cfm?Page=Calculator |dead-url= no }}</ref>

英钱最常见的缩写是“dwt”，其中“d”源自罗马的[[迪纳厄斯|迪纳厄斯]]（denarius），“d”在[[英国货币十进制日|英国货币制度改为十进制]]之前是便士的缩写。英钱的其他缩写还有“pwt”和“PW”。

== 记重之外的用途 ==
